Juan Yun: I am honored to attend this welcome feast for your guest from home and enjoy a wonderful night with you all.
Jihasaha: .........
Tindoiimu: It is only due to the Qilin Tribe's generosity that Jihasaha was able to come here. It is us who are honored.
Tingko: Actually, I told the princess that the other day you waited all afternoon for her. She felt bad and figured you should come tonight!
Tindoiimu: Oh Tingko, you don't need to bring that up...!
Juan Yun: Ah, I see. I was wondering why the princess went out of her way to invite me~
Juan Yun: Tindoiimu, you don't have to feel bad. That was my choice.
Tindoiimu: ...O-Oh, yes, of course...
Tingko: A-A-Assassin... there's an assassin!
Tindoiimu: (This fake assassin is so weak... Tingko, couldn't you find anyone more believable...?)
Jihasaha: Argh!
Assassin: Eh? How'd you... no, here's my chance!
Assassin: Princess of the Insect Tribe, you shall be buried here today!
Juan Yun: Are you okay?
Tindoiimu: You...
Assassin: Damn...!
Juan Yun: After him!
Juan Yun: Apologies—you are an esteemed guest of the Qilin Tribe, and these incidents keep occurring within our borders...
Juan Yun: I will catch the assassin. I give you my word.
Juan Yun: Jihasaha, please keep her safe.
Tindoiimu: Didn't think... he'd risk his life for me like that...
Tingko: Yeah, seriously...
Tingko: Looks like the princess' plan has—
Tindoiimu: ─Jihasaha, it's up to you now.
Jihasaha: Princess, perhaps we should think this over.
Tindoiimu: Just do it, before they come back.
Jihasaha: ...Yes, princess.
Tindoiimu: Agh!!
Juan Yun: Princess, the assassin scaled a wall and escaped. I'm afraid I've lost him...
Juan Yun: Are you hurt!? How could this be!?
Tindoiimu: I think... there were others hiding here. They emerged after you left, catching us off guard...
Tindoiimu: Thankfully, Jihasaha was here. He was able to force them out.
Jihasaha: No. I was much too careless. I was unable to adequately protect the princess. Please, punish me for my ineptitude!
Juan Yun: No. Both of us were careless.
Juan Yun: Having a feast outside like this, we are far too exposed. I should have anticipated this...
Juan Yun: More importantly—How is her injury, Doctor?

Physician: The muscles and bones have not been affected, but she will need at least a month's rest. 

It would be best to refrain from moving too much, so the wound does not tear.
Tindoiimu: Does that mean... the wind shaman...
Juan Yun: Obviously, it would be terrible of me to force you... It is most important that you heal. I suppose Himawari will have to be wind shaman now.
Tindoiimu: Yes. Miss Himawari is best suited for the... Agh!
Tingko: Princess, you need to rest!
Tindoiimu: Yes...
Juan Yun: Guards, please help the princess back to her quarters.
Tindoiimu: Thank you, Lord Juan Yun...
Juan Yun: (I never thought she'd go to such great lengths to refuse me. She doesn't realize her own potential...)
Juan Yun: (I truly hope that she can have more faith in herself...)
